response「An enum is a better fit when the set of possible values is fixed and known at compile time, because it allows compile-time dispatch and stronger type safety. The tradeoff is that it is less flexible than `Box<dyn Trait>` when the set of possible behaviors is dynamic or unknown at compile time. A rule of thumb is to use an enum when the variant set is small and stable, and use trait objects when the behavior set is larger or more dynamic.」
※ [ note_enum_dispatch ]
